==English==
===Etymology===
Originates 1695–1705 from [[Latin]] ''subsellia'' (low [[seat]] or [[bench]]), from ''[[sub-]]'' (under) + ''[[sella]]'' ([[seat]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun|subsellia}}
# A projecting ledge on the [[stall]]s in a [[church]] where persons might lean whilst standing during prayers; [[misericord]].

